post_text:
The District is looking for talented individuals to join our team. Positions in all areas are available. Please check out our available positions at the following link.

If you are looking for a more flexible work schedule, becoming a substitute teacher, paraprofessional, or secretary may be the option for you. Recently the State of Iowa changed the requirements to become a substitute teacher to make more people eligible to be in our classrooms. To learn more please contact Jenn Herrera at herrera.jennifer@iowacityschools.org. There are numerous substitute authorization classes happening now.

post_text:
Many members of our school district community have expressed grief, sadness, indignation, anger, and even numbness in the wake of a series of recent tragic incidents of anti-black and racialized violence and dehumanization. For those hoping that the future will bring something brighter for our students, families, and staff, these events may simply feel like too much to process when added to the disproportionalities bearing out in this pandemic and the ongoing trauma of inequities in our systems.

Please know that we are thinking of you and that you are not alone in this moment. We all deserve to be safe and secure. This District will not tolerate racism, hate, and other discriminatory acts. Our hearts hurt for you and we are committed to actions that will help us see the change that is long overdue. As a community, it is upon us to work for a better tomorrow and to come together to create just that. With the summer now upon us, please know that we are still here and would encourage you to reach out if there is any way we can assist you. #ICCSDtogether

shared_text:
O'Brien Family McDonald's
April 9 at 5:50 PM ·

Today we treated the wonderful group of people in the Iowa City Community School District that are continuing to put together food for the students to be able to pick up for free through the closure! This was a well deserved treat for a group of people working hard every day! #mcdonaldscares #lovinourcommunity

If you have a direct contact for a school district that is doing this in one our communities, please message it to us through Facebook, so we can get in contact with them to set up a delivery. Please provide to us the school district, contact name, and phone number and/or email address. Thanks!

post_text:
We have established drive-through or walk-up meal pick-up locations at a number of District sites while schools are closed.

Beginning Monday, March 23, 2020, the following schools will provide both lunch for the day and breakfast for the following day. Meals will be distributed between 11 am and 1 pm. Families are asked to stay in their car and wait for the meals to be brought to the vehicle and passed through the window. The District will provide a number of meals based on the number of children in the car ages 1-18. Per USDA federal guidelines, children must be present in order for meals to be provided.

Meal Pick-up School Sites:
City High School
Hills Elementary School
North Central Junior High School
Northwest Junior High School
Twain Elementary School
West High School
Wood Elementary School

In addition, the District will also have meal pick-up sites available in the following areas:

Breckenridge Mobile Home Park
Cole/Thatcher Mobile Home Park
Lakeridge Mobile Home Park
Regency Mobile Home Park

Calling all aspiring teachers! The Iowa City Community School District will be hosting a Teacher Job Fair on Monday, December 16, 2019. We are looking to hire daily substitute teachers, long-term substitute teachers, and individuals in high need areas like Special Education, ELL and more. The district will also be considering applicants for the 2020-21 school year.

To participate in the event please apply online at https://iowacity.tedk12.com/hire/index.aspx.
Please select the December Teacher Job Fair position along with any others that may be of interest to you.

As a part of the experience, candidates will have the opportunity to interview with ICCSD school and district administrators. You will also be able to participate in the substitute teaching orientation following your interview. This will allow you to begin as a substitute teacher as soon as the appropriate documentation is received and the background check is completed.

Any questions related to this event or general employment, please contact Nick Proud at proud.nick@iowacityschools.org.

post_text: Congratulations to City High English Teacher Mandy Sotillo on receiving the District Shine Award! "I had her in one of her classes and I loved it. The atmosphere in her classroom is different from other classrooms. There are many good words to describe Mrs. Sotillo, but the three words I would use to describe her would be caring, incredible, and a good friend."
